\title{Untitled}

\taxon{skill}

\subtree{
\title{Emacspeak Binaural Beat Theme}
\p{Replace emacspeak's auditory icons with binaural beats using the \strong{intended} sound theme system.}

\subtree{
\title{Architecture}
\p{Emacspeak has three separate sound systems:}

\pre{\startverb
| System | Mechanism | What you hear |
|--------|-----------|---------------|
| **Auditory icons** | OGG files from theme dir, served to TTS server via `p <filename>` | Chimes on navigation, actions |
| **Pure tones** | `dtk-tone` → `t <pitch> <dur>` to TTS server → `tonePlayer.playPureTone` | Beeps on empty lines, case changes |
| **Soundscapes** | Boodler ambient audio mapped to major modes via UNIX socket | Continuous background audio |
\stopverb}

\p{On macOS with SwiftMac, \code{\startverbswiftmac-configure-tts\stopverb} forces \code{\startverbemacspeak-play-program\stopverb} to \code{\startverbnil\stopverb}, routing ALL auditory icons through SwiftMac's OGG player. This is the sound you hear during normal editing.}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Intended Customization Path}
\p{Emacspeak's designed mechanism for changing sounds:}

\ol{
\li{Create a directory under \code{\startverb~/emacspeak/sounds/<theme-name>/\stopverb}}
\li{Populate with \code{\startverb.ogg\stopverb} files named after the 56 standard icons}
\li{Call \code{\startverb(emacspeak-sounds-select-theme (expand-file-name "<theme-name>" emacspeak-sounds-dir))\stopverb}}
}

\p{The cache rebuilds automatically. All playback paths (\code{\startverbemacspeak-icon\stopverb}, \code{\startverbemacspeak-serve-icon\stopverb}, \code{\startverbemacspeak-play-icon\stopverb}, \code{\startverbemacspeak-queue-icon\stopverb}) use the same cache.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Current Installation}
\p{Theme directory: \code{\startverb~/emacspeak/sounds/binaural/\stopverb} Generated: 56 OGG files via SoX, each a distinct binaural beat.}

\p{init.el config (after emacspeak loads):}

\pre{\startverb
(emacspeak-sounds-select-theme
 (expand-file-name "binaural" emacspeak-sounds-dir))
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Generating the Theme}
\p{Each icon gets a unique carrier frequency (100-320 Hz) and beat frequency (2-10 Hz):}

\pre{\startverb
cd ~/emacspeak/sounds/binaural
SOX=/Users/alice/.local/bin/sox
i=0
for icon in alarm alert-user ask-question ask-short-question button center \
  char close-object complete delete-object deselect-object doc ellipses \
  fill-object help item key large-movement left mark-object modified-object \
  more n-answer network-down network-up new-mail news no-answer off on \
  open-object paragraph process-active progress repeat-active repeat-end \
  repeat-start right save-object scroll search-hit search-miss section \
  select-object shutdown task-done tick-tick time tock-tock unmodified-object \
  voice-mail warn-user window-resize y-answer yank-object yes-answer; do
  carrier=$((100 + i * 4))
  beat_tenth=$((20 + (i * 7 % 80)))
  beat=$(echo "scale=1; $beat_tenth / 10" | bc)
  freq_r=$(echo "scale=1; $carrier + $beat" | bc)
  "$SOX" -n "${icon}.ogg" synth 0.15 sine "$carrier" sine "$freq_r" \
    gain -18 channels 2 fade q 0.01 0.15 0.02
  i=$((i + 1))
done
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{56 Standard Icon Names}
\pre{\startverb
alarm alert-user ask-question ask-short-question button center
char close-object complete delete-object deselect-object doc ellipses
fill-object help item key large-movement left mark-object modified-object
more n-answer network-down network-up new-mail news no-answer off on
open-object paragraph process-active progress repeat-active repeat-end
repeat-start right save-object scroll search-hit search-miss section
select-object shutdown task-done tick-tick time tock-tock unmodified-object
voice-mail warn-user window-resize y-answer yank-object yes-answer
\stopverb}

\p{Missing icons fall back to \code{\startverbbutton.ogg\stopverb} (via \code{\startverbemacspeak-sounds-cache-get\stopverb} default).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Pitfalls (Learned the Hard Way)}
\subtree{
\title{DO NOT override \code{\startverbdtk-tone\stopverb} or \code{\startverbemacspeak-icon\stopverb}}
\p{Function overrides fail silently on macOS because:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverbsox-gen-p\stopverb} / \code{\startverbsox-play\stopverb} are nil if \code{\startverb/Users/alice/.local/bin/\stopverb} isn't in \code{\startverbexec-path\stopverb} at \code{\startverbemacspeak-preamble.el\stopverb} load time}
\li{\code{\startverbstart-process\stopverb} with SoX \code{\startverbplay\stopverb} may not route audio correctly from within Emacs subprocesses}
\li{The sound you hear is auditory icons (OGGs), NOT tones — overriding \code{\startverbdtk-tone\stopverb} changes nothing audible}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{DO NOT set \code{\startverbSWIFTMAC_TONE_VOLUME=0.0\stopverb}}
\p{This env var silences more than just pure tones. Remove it.}
}

\subtree{
\title{DO NOT set \code{\startverbemacspeak-play-program\stopverb} manually on macOS}
\p{\code{\startverbswiftmac-configure-tts\stopverb} sets it to \code{\startverbnil\stopverb} during emacspeak startup. Fighting this breaks icon playback.}
}

\subtree{
\title{The icon playback dispatch}
\pre{\startverb
emacspeak-icon(icon)
  └→ emacspeak-play-program is nil? (macOS: always yes)
       └→ emacspeak-serve-icon(icon)
            └→ sends "p <filename>\n" to dtk-speaker-process (SwiftMac)
                 └→ SwiftMac plays the OGG file via AVAudioEngine
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Customization Ideas}
\subtree{
\title{Brainwave bands per icon category}
\pre{\startverb
Action icons (delete, yank, fill)  → beta beats 13-40 Hz (alertness)
Navigation icons (left, right, scroll) → alpha beats 8-12 Hz (relaxed focus)
Status icons (complete, task-done) → theta beats 4-8 Hz (satisfaction)
Warning icons (alarm, warn-user) → gamma beats 40+ Hz (attention)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Longer/shorter durations}
\p{Adjust \code{\startverbsynth 0.15\stopverb} — current is 150ms. Chimes default is ~100ms.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Volume}
\p{Adjust \code{\startverbgain -18\stopverb} — lower values are quieter. Chimes use various gains.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Related Emacspeak Systems}
\ul{
\li{\strong{sox-gen.el}: T.V. Raman's binaural beat module (\code{\startverbsox-tone-binaural\stopverb}, \code{\startverbsox-binaural\stopverb}). Standalone — NOT wired into the icon system. Use \code{\startverbM-x sox-binaural\stopverb} for on-demand effects (sleep, dream, think, act, focus).}
\li{\strong{soundscape.el}: Continuous ambient audio per major mode via Boodler. Separate from icons. Toggle with \code{\startverbM-x soundscape-toggle\stopverb}.}
\li{\strong{Sound themes}: \code{\startverbchimes/\stopverb} (default), \code{\startverb3d/\stopverb} (spatial). Switch interactively: \code{\startverbM-x emacspeak-sounds-select-theme\stopverb}.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Dependencies}
\ul{
\li{SoX (\code{\startverbsox\stopverb} and \code{\startverbplay\stopverb} at \code{\startverb/Users/alice/.local/bin/\stopverb})}
\li{Emacspeak with SwiftMac TTS server}
\li{macOS (SwiftMac is macOS-only via AVSpeechSynthesizer)}
}
}
}